<tr bgcolor="#7A7AA5"><td><b>Reminder regarding "recharging" of items</b></td><td align="right"><b>09-01-2002</b></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan="2"><font size="1">Submitted by <a href="mailto:grayrage@darkenbane.com">Grayrage</a> on 09-01-2002 15:17</font><p>Back in March of last year, the Lead GM of all the servers sent me an email advising that "recharging" of items is bannable.  As this is becoming rampant on our server, I plan to email SOE about the issue, but here is the News Post regarding this:<br />
<br />
News archive <br />
  <br />
"Recharging" items confirmed to be a bannable offense. 15-03-2001 <br />
<br />
Submitted by Grayrage on 15-03-2001 15:30<br />
A common occurance these days on Rallos Zek (and many other servers) has been the "recharging" of items including (but not limited to) Egg Pumices, Conflag Wands and Golem Wands. <br />
<br />
Lead Game Master Valdelmar (Andy Kirton) addressed this issue advising: "It's a severe violation to do this and such actions if caught can lead to banning of the account." <br />
<br />
He further discussed that it will be fixed ASAP as he sees it as being unbalancing in PvP in the following statement: "I can see now that it's a <br />
huge problem given the old egg shaped pumices with instant dispell of buffs. I will make sure that this is processed asap."<br><br></td></tr>
